│ THOUGHT: The verifier crash happens because IPSCCP deduces that in the 'if' block, %a equals inttoptr(-1), and then substitutes that constant into the operand of llvm.lifetime.start,   │
│ which violates the rule that lifetime intrinsics must only reference alloca or poison. To fix this, I need to modify IPSCCP (llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/SCCP.cpp) so that when it replaces  │
│ values with constants, it avoids substituting non-alloca/non-poison into llvm.lifetime.start/end pointer operands. I'll open SCCP.cpp to inspect where replacements are applied and then │
│ implement a guard around replacement for lifetime intrinsics.                                                                                                                            │
