│ replacing any pointer-typed values with constants in SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant. This prevents SCCP from introducing invalid IR. I will add a simple guard that returns false  │
│ if the value is a pointer, then build the patch.                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '64a \  if (V->getType()->isPointerTy()) return false;' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp && submit-patch                                                                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
